
/*
 * The code snippet demonstrates how to use the [add] slot to append nodes retrieved by [get-nodes] to a specific location in the node hierarchy. It uses [get-nodes] to fetch nodes from [.arguments] and appends them to the path specified by the expression in [add]. 
 * 
 * 1. [add] - Appends nodes to the specified location in the node hierarchy.
 * 2. [get-nodes] - Retrieves nodes from the [.arguments] path to be added.
 */
add:x:./*/data.read/*/where/*
   get-nodes:x:@.arguments/*
